Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.35,0:00:04.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Encounters are mysterious!\NBut the world is even more so!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.81,0:00:06.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so glad I'm with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.94,0:00:10.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Today is a weather lady!\NPager logic will clear the heart!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.03,0:00:11.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He sees the single\Ntruth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.90,0:00:13.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and looks like a kid\Nbut has the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.78,0:00:15.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.67,0:01:54.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Weather Lady Abduction Case."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.18,0:02:04.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Towels, towels!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.60,0:02:09.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A little more and we'd\Nbe super-sopping wet...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.27,0:02:12.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The weather lady was right!\NThunderstorms this afternoon!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.86,0:02:14.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Where's Mr. Mori?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.73,0:02:17.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's on a work trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.65,0:02:21.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? There's a message on here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.91,0:02:24.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, now. Don't go touching it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.54,0:02:27.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have one message.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.54,0:02:28.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Geez.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.87,0:02:33.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello, this is\NAsano Aki from Nichiuri TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.88,0:02:37.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm calling because I need to\Nspeak with you about something urgent.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.92,0:02:41.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You appear to be out,\Nso I'll call again later.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.55,0:02:43.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who's Asano Aki?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.39,0:02:47.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The weather lady! You know,\Nshe does the weather on Nichiuri TV!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.43,0:02:51.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! She's on "News City" too!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.85,0:02:56.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's super cool! I'm a big fan of hers!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.57,0:03:00.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But what could she urgently\Nneed to talk to him about?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.74,0:03:06.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright! Let's talk with her instead,\Nas the Junior Detective League!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.91,0:03:08.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.45,0:03:09.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, now...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.08,0:03:12.75,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Nichiuri TV
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.62,0:03:12.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.75,0:03:17.88,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Asano Aki (27) Weather lady and newscaster
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.42,0:03:17.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you came all the way here in Mori-{\i1}san{\i0}'s place?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.88,0:03:23.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! If you need help, leave it\Nto us, the Junior Detective League!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.59,0:03:26.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, are you\Ngreeting children today?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.51,0:03:27.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tsukumo-{\i1}san{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.73,0:03:34.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Having to deal with kids just to gain popularity...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.77,0:03:36.61,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Tsukumo Kazumi (31) Newscaster
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.10,0:03:36.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Big-name newscasters sure have it tough!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.61,0:03:39.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yikes, what gaudy makeup.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.53,0:03:41.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's with that fingernail?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.28,0:03:43.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not what I'm doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.28,0:03:49.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Behave yourselves, kiddies.\NDon't get in the way of her work.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.33,0:03:56.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What an unpleasant person!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.75,0:04:00.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't she the person who\Ndid the news before you did?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.71,0:04:04.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. We switched\Nplaces about half a year ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.93,0:04:09.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was she what you wanted\Nto talk to Mr. Mori about?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.47,0:04:13.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No... A-Actually, uhh...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.39,0:04:17.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was wondering if Detective\NMori-{\i1}san {\i0}would be on News City!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.81,0:04:21.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aww, what a downer.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.78,0:04:24.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a relief it wasn't a case...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.91,0:04:25.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's that sound?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.61,0:04:26.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.66,0:04:29.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a pager.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.66,0:04:34.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ran-{\i1}neechan {\i0}told me to take it\Nbecause I always suddenly disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.00,0:04:35.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! You're so lucky!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.83,0:04:38.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You had a cell phone, Mitsuhiko!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.25,0:04:40.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was only a receiver!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.38,0:04:42.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it broke, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.01,0:04:44.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, for the sake of justice...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.26,0:04:46.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.05,0:04:50.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, this is the detective agency's number,\Nso it must be Ran-{\i1}neechan{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.22,0:04:55.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I know! Could you give\Nme your pager's number?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.60,0:04:59.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can contact you when I need\Nthe Junior Detective League's help!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.02,0:05:01.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Awesome! Hey, Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.40,0:05:04.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure! It's written right here!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.74,0:05:07.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.03,0:05:11.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see... Now to save\N"Junior Detective League" to my phone...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.58,0:05:15.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There we go! All done!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.54,0:05:22.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! This only shows numbers, huh?\NI used to have one, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.71,0:05:26.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My friends and I often used\Nnumbers to write messages for fun!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.55,0:05:27.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Messages?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.09,0:05:29.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if it can only display numbers,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.97,0:05:35.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you can use numbers that look\Nand sound like letters to write things!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.35,0:05:38.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For example, "428" could be read "Shibuya"!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.31,0:05:44.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,4, 2, 8... Shi-bu-ya...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.32,0:05:46.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shibuya! (a city in Tokyo) Neat!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.53,0:05:51.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, since you're here, how about\Na tour of the News City studio?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.24,0:05:53.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.24,0:05:53.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurray!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.54,0:05:56.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, just a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.41,0:05:57.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello, this is Asano.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.58,0:06:06.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. Yes. I will. Yes.\NOkay. I'll be right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.84,0:06:11.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry. I have work\Nto do, so I can't go.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.64,0:06:15.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.14,0:06:18.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Kobayashi-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.64,0:06:20.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes? What can I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.02,0:06:23.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry to ask, but could\Nyou show them to Studio A?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.44,0:06:25.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Some work just came up, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.78,0:06:27.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, it's no problem!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.28,0:06:29.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, and could you\Nget them some passes?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.86,0:06:30.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.78,0:06:32.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, shall we go?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.20,0:06:33.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurray!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.49,0:06:37.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm hungry...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.12,0:06:39.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How long is she going to make us wait?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.87,0:06:42.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry to suddenly\Nask you to stand in like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.83,0:06:45.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's fine, but what's this\Nabout Aki-{\i1}san {\i0}being threatened?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.34,0:06:46.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Threatened?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.80,0:06:50.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who are these kids?!\NThey're distracting! Get rid of them!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.38,0:06:51.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,U-Understood!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.14,0:06:57.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Running off because of a threat?!\NAki-{\i1}san {\i0}is a failure as a journalist!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.14,0:07:00.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're beginning rehearsal!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.40,0:07:07.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, Kazumi-{\i1}san {\i0}hates children.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.15,0:07:11.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say, she said Aki-{\i1}san {\i0}was threatened.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.15,0:07:11.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.99,0:07:15.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We came to see Aki-{\i1}san \N{\i0}in Detective Mori's place!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.87,0:07:17.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, the famous detective?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.99,0:07:21.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Well, just between us,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.54,0:07:24.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aki-{\i1}san{\i0}'s been getting\Nharassing letters and phone calls
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.42,0:07:28.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,ever since she started a story\Nabout a certain politician's corruption.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.55,0:07:31.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She got a letter this\Nmorning threatening to kill her
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.09,0:07:33.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,if she appeared on today's News City.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.01,0:07:39.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was this threat what\Nshe really wanted to discuss?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.47,0:07:42.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can see the News City\Nbroadcast on that TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.73,0:07:45.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I have work to do, so I'll see you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.36,0:07:52.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, do you think the\Nphone call Aki-{\i1}san {\i0}got earlier
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.74,0:07:54.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was a threatening phone call?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.87,0:07:58.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, and then that scared her...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.03,0:08:01.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No! Aki-{\i1}san {\i0}isn't a weakling like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.33,0:08:03.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You agree with me, right, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.17,0:08:06.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.96,0:08:12.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When she was on the phone then,\Nshe didn't seem afraid at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.84,0:08:17.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In fact, she sounded happy,\Nas if she had gotten a special scoop.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.85,0:08:21.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That call was probably not a threat.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.48,0:08:26.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, wait! If that call had been\Na trap to lure her somewhere--!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.07,0:08:32.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it Ran-{\i1}oneechan{\i0} again?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.28,0:08:34.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.16,0:08:40.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's probably Aki-{\i1}san{\i0}. Only she\Nand Ran-{\i1}neechan {\i0}know this number.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.54,0:08:41.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.42,0:08:50.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello, this is Asano. I'm not home\Nright now, so please leave your--
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.09,0:08:54.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Why'd you hang up?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.38,0:08:56.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was it not Aki-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.59,0:09:00.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was her home. But it\Nwas her answering machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.60,0:09:05.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's odd! Why would she have\Nyou call her home if she isn't there?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.52,0:09:12.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,110?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.73,0:09:14.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The police phone number.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.11,0:09:16.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The police?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.86,0:09:18.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why would the police call us?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.95,0:09:20.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No! It's Aki-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.08,0:09:26.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A bad guy must've caught her!\NSo she wants us to call the police!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.75,0:09:30.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then couldn't she\Njust call them herself?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.21,0:09:34.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What if she's unable to talk?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.30,0:09:41.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh no!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.56,0:09:42.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's an abduction...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.31,0:09:49.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,9109.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.35,0:09:53.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the city code of her phone number!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.23,0:09:57.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The police won't listen to us with only this.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.74,0:10:02.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If the police can't help,\Nthen the Junior Detective League will!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.20,0:10:07.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but this isn't\Nenough to know where she is.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.91,0:10:08.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.92,0:10:10.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.83,0:10:12.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And now for today's sports.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.92,0:10:17.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The J-League game at the\NNational Stadium between the Tokyo--
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.01,0:10:21.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I like Aki-{\i1}san{\i0} a lot better...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.89,0:10:25.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,2003.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.97,0:10:29.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I got it! It's read "{\i1}Niousama{\i0}"!\N[temple guardian]
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.77,0:10:32.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So she's where there\Nare temple guardian statues!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.36,0:10:36.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on. Can't you deduce\Na little better than that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.19,0:10:39.28,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Nichiuri TV
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.35,0:11:15.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The messages after\N7:20 make no sense at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.99,0:11:21.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lastly, we've just received this news.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.36,0:11:24.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Special Investig. Unit of\Nthe Tokyo Public Prosecutor's Office
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.37,0:11:27.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is to question the politicians\NMr. Maruya and Mr. Okubo tomorrow
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.45,0:11:29.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,about their possible\Nacceptance of large bribes
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.37,0:11:32.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in relation to the corruption\Ncase involving Bay Development.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.21,0:11:37.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've figured out what\NAki-{\i1}san{\i0}'s messages mean!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.13,0:11:39.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For reals, Mitsuhiko?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.17,0:11:43.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These are indicating the names\Nof the politicians who took bribes!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.09,0:11:47.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,0 is "maru". Maruya's initial, basically!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.47,0:11:50.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,00 is "oo." Okubo's initial!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.81,0:11:53.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the 96 of 096 is "kuro"!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.69,0:12:00.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So Aki-{\i1}san {\i0}is trying to say\Nit's Maruya who's guilty of corruption!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.65,0:12:04.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what do 2003 and 5656 mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.61,0:12:09.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're bank account numbers\Nused for the bribes, of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.29,0:12:15.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright! Aki-{\i1}san {\i0}must be\Ncaptured at Maruya's home then!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.75,0:12:17.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's hurry and save her!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.38,0:12:22.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard he lives in West Teitan,\None subway stop from here!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.22,0:12:25.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.59,0:12:27.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.73,0:12:35.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now there's thunder! Let's run, guys!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.78,0:12:44.49,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Maruya
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.78,0:12:49.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Conan! Hurry up! Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.49,0:12:52.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Keep watch for anyone coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.70,0:12:54.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mitsuhiko! Hurry up here!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.33,0:12:55.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.87,0:13:01.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you! What are you doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.09,0:13:02.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come down here!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.93,0:13:08.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.60,0:13:12.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can't believe you\Nguys ran off without me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.68,0:13:17.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, we'll have to do something\Nabout the guard and the dogs.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.40,0:13:20.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You saw them first!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.02,0:13:22.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.19,0:13:24.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aki-{\i1}san{\i0}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.15,0:13:26.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's Ran-{\i1}neechan{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.20,0:13:28.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.28,0:13:29.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go call her!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.70,0:13:37.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aww, it's raining again...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.67,0:13:39.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello? Ran-{\i1}neechan{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.67,0:13:41.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.13,0:13:43.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you at this time of night?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.34,0:13:45.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I paged you and paged you,\Nbut you ignored me!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.67,0:13:49.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,S-Sorry! I'll be home soon!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.05,0:13:50.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You better come home quick!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.02,0:13:58.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? There's thunder where you are?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.85,0:14:01.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yea, it's really rainy and thundery.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.86,0:14:05.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's nice weather here.\NThe moon is really pretty!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.61,0:14:10.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's pouring here, so I don't\Nthink I'll be home for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.28,0:14:12.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you right now, Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.95,0:14:15.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Should I bring an\Numbrella and come get you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.83,0:14:18.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Moon?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.75,0:14:24.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? Hello? Conan-{\i1}kun{\i0}? \NHey, are you listening to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.63,0:14:26.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now for tomorrow's weather.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.80,0:14:30.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A cold front in the northern Kanto\Nregion will bring clouds and rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.64,0:14:35.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Southern Kanto will have clear skies.\NTomorrow's high temperature...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.98,0:14:43.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're going back to the TV station!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.65,0:14:46.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry, everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.11,0:14:47.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait up!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.53,0:14:49.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You better explain, Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.79,0:15:00.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here, try reading 2003 on its side.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.54,0:15:02.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On its side?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.54,0:15:05.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,M-O-O-N.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.75,0:15:09.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I get it! Awesome!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.67,0:15:11.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, what's that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.68,0:15:14.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It spells "moon" in English.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.14,0:15:20.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, the reason Aki-{\i1}san\N{\i0}sent this "2003" message first
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.31,0:15:23.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was because she wanted\Nus to look up at the night sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.48,0:15:27.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The "2003" was displayed at 7:20 pm.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.53,0:15:31.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As I recall, the moon\Nwas in the southeast then.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.82,0:15:34.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it wasn't visible\Nfrom Maruya's mansion,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.57,0:15:37.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,because of buildings to the southeast.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.83,0:15:42.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means Aki-{\i1}san\N{\i0}isn't at Maruya's home, right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.42,0:15:47.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right... she's being held somewhere\Nwhere she can see the moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.34,0:15:50.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that isn't enough to\Ntell us where she is.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.92,0:15:51.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.97,0:15:54.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So she used numbers like weather symbols
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.97,0:15:58.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to indicate weather\Nchanges where she is!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.97,0:16:01.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,0 is the circle meaning fair weather.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.48,0:16:04.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,00 is the double-circle\Nmeaning cloudy weather.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.94,0:16:09.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,096 is a filled circle, meaning rain!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.69,0:16:14.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What about the 5656 at 8:31?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.61,0:16:16.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Say the sound effect for thunder out loud.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.95,0:16:19.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Goro (56) goro (56)"...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.91,0:16:23.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I get it! 5656 was referring to thunder!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.83,0:16:26.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yep!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.71,0:16:33.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So she's being held where there\Nwas rain and thunder around 8:30!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.98,0:16:45.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Places with thunderstorms at 8:30 pm?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.98,0:16:50.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, the only one was the area around this TV station
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.94,0:16:50.98,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Nichiuri TV Meteorology Center
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.98,0:16:52.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,within a 1-kilometer radius!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.28,0:16:54.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was a passing shower!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.53,0:16:55.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.03,0:17:01.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just as you thought!\NAki-{\i1}san {\i0}is somewhere in this area!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.70,0:17:03.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.46,0:17:09.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,0109... What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.25,0:17:11.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wouldn't 01 be the symbol\Nfor "clear weather"?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.55,0:17:16.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's still cloudy here.\NIt must mean something different.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.80,0:17:21.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I bet 0109 means, "I want\Nto eat a huge eel box lunch!"
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.43,0:17:24.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, she's probably hungry!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.64,0:17:26.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think you mean you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.31,0:17:30.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm hungry...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.45,0:17:39.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's your problem?!\NIt's not that funny!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.28,0:17:43.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, sorry! That's not it!\NNice work, Genta!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.29,0:17:47.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks to you, I know where Aki-{\i1}san {\i0}is!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.06,0:18:09.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The large prop room?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.10,0:18:11.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! That's where\Nwe got separated from her!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.15,0:18:15.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As I recall, it's the northernmost\Nroom on the first floor...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.61,0:18:16.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.49,0:18:17.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.95,0:18:20.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aki-{\i1}san{\i0}'s in the large prop room!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.32,0:18:26.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like Genta said, you read the 0,\N10, and 9 of that 0109 separately!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.58,0:18:31.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,0, 10, 9? O... to... ku?\NOdogu! (large prop)
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.71,0:18:35.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are lots of rooms in\NTV stations that people rarely enter!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.00,0:18:38.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If the kidnapper works here,\Nthey could use one!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.84,0:18:41.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does that mean you know who it is?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.10,0:18:45.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, because Aki-{\i1}san {\i0}told us who!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.32,0:18:56.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,End of the line!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.66,0:19:02.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's no use running.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.57,0:19:04.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We know everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.37,0:19:05.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give yourself up.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.54,0:19:10.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You called Aki-{\i1}san {\i0}here,\Nknocked her out with drugs or something,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.21,0:19:13.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and locked her in that back room
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.50,0:19:17.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to make others think she had run away,\Nout of fear of that threat.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.46,0:19:23.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, you tried to ruin her credibility\Nand have her kicked off News City!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.72,0:19:29.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aki-{\i1}san {\i0}used her cell phone to\Nsend us messages about her location
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.93,0:19:33.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,by referencing weather changes\Nshe could see outside the window!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.94,0:19:39.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Except, there was one message\Nshe sent that I didn't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.69,0:19:41.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,9109.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.74,0:19:49.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This number came in after\Na message to call the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.75,0:19:54.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, if it didn't indicate her location...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.83,0:19:56.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...it indicated her kidnapper's name!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.25,0:19:59.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no, you don't!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.67,0:20:03.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take this!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.85,0:20:12.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're the Junior Detective League!\NThere's no getting away from us!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.77,0:20:14.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.77,0:20:17.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aki-{\i1}san{\i0}! Hang on! Aki-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.15,0:20:27.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,9109 is separated as 9-10-9.\NChanged to kanji and read aloud...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.62,0:20:31.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,... "tsu ku mo."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.87,0:20:34.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That would be you,\NTsukumo Kazumi-{\i1}san{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.54,0:20:39.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get off me!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.80,0:20:46.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just couldn't stand it...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.30,0:20:52.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,News City was my idea!\NIt was my show from the start!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.73,0:20:59.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But then they replaced me with\Nsomeone younger, someone cuter!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.02,0:21:04.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is serious business! This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.53,0:21:09.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then earn the spot back with actual skill.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.79,0:21:17.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However you rationalize it,\Na crime can't be justified.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.06,0:22:58.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That concludes this\Nafternoon's weather forecast!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.35,0:22:59.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And cut!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.89,0:23:01.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good work!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.98,0:23:03.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry for the wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.44,0:23:08.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you all so much for yesterday!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.32,0:23:12.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But only the Junior Detective\NLeague could've realized
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.91,0:23:15.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that my messages were weather codes!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.29,0:23:20.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But how did you know it was Kazumi-{\i1}san{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.83,0:23:24.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When she tried to put me to sleep,\NI caught a glimpse of her nails.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.08,0:23:27.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! The nail art!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.42,0:23:34.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yep! The design reminded me of\Na weather map, so I remembered it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.85,0:23:36.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That means you're\Nsnow pellets, Genta-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.81,0:23:37.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Snow pellets?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.47,0:23:38.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.10,0:23:44.11,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Snow Pellets
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.58,0:23:47.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah! That image fits you perfectly!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.98,0:23:49.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.36,0:23:55.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Genta. You're not just snow pellets.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.49,0:24:01.12,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Hail
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.08,0:24:00.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hail!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.85,0:24:14.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks pretty tense.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.18,0:24:18.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who is that man with the long hair?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.21,0:24:23.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's this doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.56,0:24:25.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.30,0:24:27.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the next Conan:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.74,0:24:31.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A Mysterious Sniper Murder Case, Part One.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.16,0:24:49.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's hint:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.58,0:24:51.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Spotlight.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.68,0:24:53.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next episode is an original story.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.16,0:24:54.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.43,0:24:55.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.75,0:24:56.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.85,0:24:58.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
